The Medal of Independence.

29
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,480
Just to thank me for saving his life.

30
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:21,660
Dad, there are some urgent matters at the company.

31
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:28,020
Is it so important that you have to go?

32
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:31,060
Can't you just ask someone else to take care of it?

33
00:02:31,940 --> 00:02:34,400
Yuncheng, today is Grandpa's birthday.

34
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,700
No matter how urgent it is, it can wait.

35
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:41,360
How about you wait until you finish eating Grandpa's birthday cake?

36
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:45,480
It's okay. If the young people are busy, just let them go first.

37
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:48,100
I have Yunzheng here.

38
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,500
You can go.

39
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,180
Jiang Jiang.

40
00:03:35,437 --> 00:03:37,530
Why are you here?

41
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:39,300
It's so late. Where'd you go?

42
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:41,020
I've been waiting for you all night, where have you been?

43
00:03:41,020 --> 00:03:43,780
- I'm asking you. 
 - No, I'm asking you.

44
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:49,460
I just came back, so I went to see people's nightlife. Can't I?

45
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:51,260
Really?

46
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:52,340
When did you come back?

47
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:53,560
You're not there.

48
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:56,400
I'm by myself, so what's the point of me staying in that place?

49
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,260
So I came back.

50
00:03:57,260 --> 00:04:00,080
But isn't Fang Mingfan still there?

51
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:05,790
How far have you two progressed?

52
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:08,820
I've succeeded.

53
00:04:08,820 --> 00:04:12,000
Really? That's great.

54
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:15,060
You've dragged this process on so long.

55
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:18,860
What? He always wants me to be responsible for him, you know?

56
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:21,000
He's a grown man. What can I do for him?

57
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,620
But I just went with the flow and won him over.

58
00:04:23,620 --> 00:04:25,600
That's great.

59
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,580
So he's back too?

60
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:33,920
Yes, he is.

61
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,840
Okay, don't leave tonight. I'll sleep with you in my arms.

62
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:43,460
I wasn't planning to leave tonight.

63
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:55,300
It's too early.

64
00:04:55,740 --> 00:05:00,160
In the end, I went from Lakaya to Jinhai.

65
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:03,080
What? What Lakaya?

66
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,360
What did you say?

67
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:08,640
Sister Lan, good morning. You're up so early.

68
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:13,340
Shakespeare. We were just saying,

69
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:17,620
I mean, next to Paris VI University, there's a Shakespeare bookstore.

70
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:20,540
And we often go there for coffee.

71
00:05:20,540 --> 00:05:22,560
- Right. 
 - And to read some books.

72
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,760
Really?

73
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:31,380
Tell me, when you were reading, were there any foreign boys pursuing her?

74
00:05:31,380 --> 00:05:33,200
She's too embarrassed to tell me.

75
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:38,040
If I find out that you're not serious about dating, I'll skin you.

76
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,360
- Yes. 
 - Really?

77
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,440
And there's quite a lot.

78
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:45,240
Really? Come on, hurry up. Let’s talk about it.

79
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:49,320
Wei'an just wouldn't tell me.

80
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:52,860
Tell me, what kind of person is he?

81
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:58,480
It's a Frenchman. His name is Eliot.

82
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,980
He's a famous French doctor.

83
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:04,040
You have no idea, those eyes of his are deep and charming.

84
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:08,160
After you see him, your soul will be hooked away.

85
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,840
So handsome? French people are good.

86
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,800
They are romantic and sentimental.

87
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:15,920
But Auntie, he's a bit too romantic.

88
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:21,360
When we went to a dance, he pulled over a girl and kissed her right away.

89
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,880
And he almost kissed me.

90
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,040
I was so scared that I quickly grabbed Wei'an and ran.

91
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,880
That's not good. We can't accept that.

92
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,260
No matter how handsome he is, he's not good.

93
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:29,880
You're right.

94
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,440
Help me think.

95
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:34,640
Did anyone give her a stone?

96
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,020
A stone?

97
00:06:37,020 --> 00:06:40,520
It's like... Wait, I'll show you.

98
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:47,170
It's this. Take a look.

99
00:06:47,170 --> 00:06:48,095
This...

100
00:06:48,095 --> 00:06:49,020
Do you know?

101
00:06:49,020 --> 00:06:51,060
Let me think.

102
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:56,660
We went mountain climbing.

103
00:06:56,660 --> 00:07:02,520
On the mountain, there was a large wishing pool.

104
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:04,760
This was picked up from the wishing pool.

105
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,020
Picked up? It was picked up?

106
00:07:06,020 --> 00:07:09,840
Yes, I remember. This one is for attracting peach blossoms. 
  (TN: For lovers)

107
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:12,040
It's for lovers?

108
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:15,720
But why did Wei'an say it's for attracting wealth?

109
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,720
Auntie, she's embarrassed to tell you.

110
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:24,560
She must be afraid that she won't be able to attract a peach blossom, and then you'll scold her.

111
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:27,360
Really? Attracting peach blossoms are good.

112
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,920
I almost threw it away accidentally.

113
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,920
I need to find a good place for it.

114
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,980
I'll put it here. Next to the first place trophy.

115
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:35,440
Okay.

116
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:39,940
Please help my daughter find a good man.

117
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,340
Help me think about it again.

118
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:47,960
Is there anyone named Yun or Zheng?

119
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:52,260
Mom, why are you asking her this?

120
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:54,333
Is the food ready? I'm starving.

121
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:57,580
No, there's plenty of food in the kitchen. Go find some yourself.

122
00:07:57,580 --> 00:08:00,820
How would I know if I didn't ask? We're caring about you.

123
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:04,500
If you try hard on your own, would we have to worry about you here?

124
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,800
- Right? 
 - Exactly.

125
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:11,440
Look. Think about it for me, is there someone named Yun or...?

126
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:15,400
Auntie, the one you're talking about is Du Yuncheng.

127
00:08:16,340 --> 00:08:18,480
It does seem a bit like this name.

128
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:22,590
Yes, it must be him. He's Wei'an's senior in college.

129
00:08:22,590 --> 00:08:26,750
Also, back in school, he confessed his love to her in public.

130
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,160
He did?

131
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:31,660
And then?

132
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:36,240
By the way, Wei'an, didn’t you say that he's now the CEO of some Jiehui?

133
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,280
What's going on?

134
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,770
He's even a CEO?

135
00:08:38,770 --> 00:08:42,040
No wonder he's a CEO. He has good taste.

136
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:44,840
He chose our Wei'an among all the people.

137
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:47,380
He already has a girlfriend.

138
00:08:47,380 --> 00:08:49,280
He has a girlfriend?

139
00:08:53,605 --> 00:08:54,540
That's not right.

140
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:57,940
If he has a girlfriend, why do you call his name in your dreams?

141
00:08:57,940 --> 00:09:00,120
Call what name?

142
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,840
No way. I only met him once after I came back.

143
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,900
But I heard it myself.

144
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:06,460
It was so clear.

145
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:07,500
Yuncheng.

146
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,940
Mom!

147
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:11,400
Square dance.

148
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,760
I'm late.

149
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,540
I've already prepared the food. Help yourselves.

150
00:09:14,540 --> 00:09:15,580
Hurry up and go.

151
00:09:15,580 --> 00:09:17,560
Tell me when I come back.

152
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,860
Scared me to death.

153
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,480
I was wrong.

154
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:33,920

155
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:45,040

156
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:52,360
 She left?

157
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,080
 Where did she go?

158
00:09:57,420 --> 00:09:59,460
 Where did she go?

159
00:09:59,460 --> 00:10:01,160
 Where did she go?

160
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:04,600
 How do I know where she's going?

161
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,000
Boss.

162
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:12,680
What are you thinking about?

163
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:14,880
Mind your own business.

164
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:18,200
I know even if you don’t tell me. Follow me.

165
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,320
Where to?

166
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,940
The psychiatric department.

167
00:10:20,940 --> 00:10:22,700
You should know.

168
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:26,920
After the medical aid team returns, they all have to take a mental health test.

169
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:30,240
I heard they hired a very good doctor from Harvard Medical School.

170
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:33,880
Just in time to also take a look at your other psychological problems.

171
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:35,400
Let's go.

172
00:10:36,420 --> 00:10:38,220
Dr. Gu.

173
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:41,080
What a coincidence.

174
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:45,640
I thought you weren't coming back this year.

175
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:48,900
From Dr. He's tone, it doesn't seem like you didn't want me to come back.

176
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,360
How could that be?

177
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,115
I miss you very much.

178
00:10:52,115 --> 00:10:53,780
Without you here, I have one less competitor.

179
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:56,420
Life is tasteless.

180
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:00,540
It seems like I've been away from China for too long.

181
00:11:00,540 --> 00:11:05,000
I don’t even know when Dr. He became so confident.

182
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:09,060
When did you qualify to be my competitor?

183
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,840
Things are different now, don't you know?

184
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:18,060
The selections for the Young Talent Fund will start soon.

185
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:21,866
No matter what president or chief you saved in Lakaya, or what medal you got,

186
00:11:21,866 --> 00:11:23,100
it's no use.

187
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:26,440
What this selection relies on is scientific research ability.

188
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,520
Look at how much time you've wasted in Lakaya.

189
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,220
And I've been constantly making progress here.

190
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:34,500
So this time, I won't lose to you.

191
00:11:37,065 --> 00:11:38,865
Goodbye.

192
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,840
So irritating.

193
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,380
Boss, just ignore him.

194
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:49,000
This guy is out of his mind.

195
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,220
Why would I care about him?

196
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:54,200
He's someone who just idles his time away.

197
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:58,400
No wonder, even though I've been away for so long, I've never seen any of his papers published in the SCI  (Science Citation Index) .

198
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,780
Right. Just ignore him.

199
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:03,940
Come with me.

200
00:12:03,940 --> 00:12:05,720
- Let's go. 
 - I said I don't want to go.

201
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,420
You'll see when you get there.

202
00:12:07,420 --> 00:12:09,120
Here we are.

203
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,700
Right here.

204
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:18,165
Dr. Gu, are you guys here for a mental health test?

205
00:12:18,165 --> 00:12:19,120
Yes.

206
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:21,660
Then have a seat over there first.

207
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:26,380
You're still so popular, even after being away.

208
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:33,820
- Thanks. 
 - Did you two both go on the medical aid mission to Lakaya?

209
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:35,480
- Yes. 
 - How long have you been back?

210
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,520
We just came back two weeks ago.

211
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:38,780
Then you two can drink some water and wait here.

212
00:12:38,780 --> 00:12:40,460
Professor Li has already been notified.

213
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:42,040
Okay.

214
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:47,720
The environment here is really a lot better.

215
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:50,420
This chair is more comfortable than the beds in our lounge.

216
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:55,360
Boss, how much higher do you think the salary is for this female doctor from Harvard compared to ours?

217
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,580
This looks very luxurious.

218
00:12:57,580 --> 00:13:00,400
Being in the International Department, it must be at one's own expense.

219
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:02,460
If you ask me, mental illness is a disease of the rich.

220
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:04,600
Boss, you really have to check it out later.

221
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:09,080
Fang Mingfan, can you please shut up?

222
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,780
Hello, you two. I'm Li Wantong.

223
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:20,840
Hello.

224
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:24,480
You're that female doctor who came back from Harvard Medical School?

225
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,460
Yes.

226
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:29,280
I joined Huaren Hospital not long ago. Please take good care of me.

227
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:36,040
Dr. Gu Yunzheng. I read your paper on glioma in The Lancet. 
  (TN: A medical journal)

228
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,620
I've long admired you.

229
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:43,320
You have a Ph.D. in psychology, but you read a thesis on glioma? 
  (A growth of cells that starts in the brain or spinal cord.)

230
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:46,000
Psychology is also an important branch of medicine.

231
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:50,880
As a doctor, it's necessary to have a comprehensive understanding of cutting-edge research in various disciplines.

232
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:53,560
All right. Then let's go over there, gentlemen.

233
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,280
Let's go, Boss.

234
00:14:02,420 --> 00:14:05,180
Has Dr. Gu encountered any setbacks recently?

235
00:14:05,180 --> 00:14:08,540
I mean, in the emotional aspect.

236
00:14:08,540 --> 00:14:09,680
No.

237
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:11,600
Besides a slightly elevated anxiety index

238
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,160
and a short-term sensitivity to interpersonal relationships,

239
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:17,300
the scores for the other items are all excellent.

240
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:20,400
So did I pass the test?

241
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:23,680
Your mental health is good and your ability to handle stress is strong.

242
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:27,280
As for short-term mood swings, I think you can make adjustments yourself.

243
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:30,700
Thank you, Dr. Li. I'll go back to my office then.

244
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,500
Wait a minute.

245
00:14:34,260 --> 00:14:36,240
Is there something else?

246
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:43,060
The Psychiatry Department, in addition to operating externally, also provides free psychological consultations for our hospital's doctors.

247
00:14:43,060 --> 00:14:47,800
I think maybe one day, you will need this service.

248
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:51,240
- So... 
 - So I want to apologize to you in advance.

249
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:56,360
If that day really comes, I may not be able to consult you personally.

250
00:14:57,680 --> 00:14:58,620
Why?

251
00:14:58,620 --> 00:15:03,180
Because there can't be any emotional relationship between the counselor and the patient.

252
00:15:03,180 --> 00:15:08,120
And I'm sure we're about to get into a relationship.

253
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:19,660
Dr. Li, it hasn't been more than 30 minutes since we met.

254
00:15:19,660 --> 00:15:22,600
I'm pretty sure we won't be getting into an emotional relationship.

255
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:26,300
But, I've known you for more than 30 minutes.

256
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:31,620
Before I met you, I screened the profiles of all single male doctors in the hospital system.

